" [FBC:DOS]\nis_a: UBERON:0034926 ! anatomical row\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002536 ! arthropod sensillum\nrelationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:50557 ! Insecta\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8440015\nname: noradrenergic cell groups\ndef: \"Collections of neurons in the central nervous system that have been demonstrated by histochemical fluorescence to contain the neurotransmitter norepinephrine (noradrenalin).\" [WikipediaVersioned:Noradrenergic_cell_groups&oldid=965992184]\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000459 ! noradrenergic cell\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8480034\nname: intralobular stroma of mammary gland\ndef: \"The intralobular stroma of the mammary gland lobule contains loosely connected fibroblasts. It is surrounded by the more compact interlobular stroma.\" [PMID:18710550]\nis_a: UBERON:0003584 ! mammary gland connective tissue\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000057 ! fibroblast\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0819-0473 ! Paula Duek Roggli\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2022-10-03T14:38:17Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600004\nname: visceral muscle tissue\ndef: \"A muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).\" [BTO:0002780, CLAO:0001295]\ncomment: It is quite common to refer to visceral muscles as smooth muscles, by analogy with vertebrates; however, most visceral muscles in arthropods are actually striated. {xref=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smooth_muscle\", xref=\"FBbt:00005070\", comment=\"PMID:8720463\"}\nsynonym: \"visceral muscle\" EXACT [] {comment=\"BTO:0002780\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0002385 ! muscle tissue\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0008007 ! visceral muscle cell\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-02-16T10:17:46Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600026\nname: chorionic villous tree\ndef: \"A tree-like structure formed by chorionic villi that sprouts from the chorionic plate in the placental disc. The arborous shape of the chorionic villous tree provides maximal contact area with maternal blood in the intervillous space.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"placental villous tree\" EXACT [PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"villous tree\" BROAD [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0000061 ! anatomical structure\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600038 ! placental disc\nrelationship: proximally_connected_to UBERON:0004027 ! chorionic plate\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T11:57:24Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600050\nname: trophoblast island\ndef: \"An accumulation of extravillous trophoblast cells at the tip of a floating villus or occasionally attached to the chorionic plate embedded in fibrin.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\ncomment: A trophoblast island is directly continuous with villous cytotrophoblast in places where the villous syncytiotrophoblast is interrupted. {xref=\"doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8\"}\nsynonym: \"cell island\" RELATED [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"intraplacental trophoblast island\" EXACT [PMID:33218578]\nsynonym: \"trophoblastic cell island\" EXACT [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0000061 ! anatomical structure\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000351 ! trophoblast cell\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: located_in UBERON:8600025 ! intervillous space\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-04-15T10:05:35Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Typedef]\nid: composed_primarily_of\nname: composed primarily of\nxref: RO:0002473\n\n","exit":0,"description":"Inspect composed primarily usage","truncated":true,"outputPath":"/github/home/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e0f97fe60001SvyVuQL230z2jq"}